"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Recipes","item":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Paleo Recipes","item":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":4,"name":"Paleo Desserts","item":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo/desserts/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":5,"name":"Paleo Raspberry Coconut Cake"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/#website","url":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/","name":"Cooked & Loved","description":"Delicious Recipes With A Healthy Twist","potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/search/{search_term_string}"},"query-input":"required name=search_term_string"}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/#/schema/person/3bbd3151d0cf4b3a3749c05d64101243","name":"Irena Macri","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/#/schema/person/image/","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8f6e71b3e1a68ce60a934deef8811623?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8f6e71b3e1a68ce60a934deef8811623?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Irena Macri"},"url":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/author/imacri/"},{"@context":"https://schema.org/","@type":"Recipe","name":"Raspberry Coconut Cake (Paleo, Gluten-free)","description":"Learn how to make a delicious raspberry coconut cake that is paleo, gluten-free and grain-free. It's low in calories and carbohydrates, too.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Irena Macri"},"image":["https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/paleo-coconut-raspberry-cake-h-225x225.jpg","https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/paleo-coconut-raspberry-cake-h-260x195.jpg","https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/paleo-coconut-raspberry-cake-h-320x180.jpg","https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/paleo-coconut-raspberry-cake-h.jpg"],"url":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/","recipeIngredient":["1 cup almond meal/ground almonds","1/2 cup unsweetened desiccated coconut (shredded is fine)","1/4 cup coconut flour","1/2 teaspoon gluten-free baking powder","4 medium eggs","Zest of 1 orange","1 tablespoon of vanilla extract","1/2 cup melted coconut oil","1 tablespoon orange juice","1 tablespoon lemon juice","4 tablespoons rice malt syrup or raw honey","1/2 cup fresh raspberries, plus extra to have on the side"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat the oven to 175-180¬∞C / 350¬∞F (conventional). Grease an 8-inch springform cake tin with coconut oil and place a round piece of baking/parchment paper on the bottom.","url":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/#instruction-step-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Combine almond meal, desiccated coconut, coconut flour and baking powder in a large mixing bowl, making sure there are no clumps.","url":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/#instruction-step-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Whisk the eggs in a another bowl until frothy. Add the orange zest, vanilla, melted coconut oil (I warmed it up in a small saucepan), orange and lemon juice, and rice malt syrup or other sweetener of your choice. Whisk well, for about a minute.","url":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/#instruction-step-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour and whisk the egg mixture into the dry ingredients. Combine and fold together until thick and well incorporated. Transfer the mixture into the prepared cake tin, scrapping every last bit from the sides.","url":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/#instruction-step-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a snail pattern, insert raspberries almost all the way through with just the tops sticking out. Place the cake in the oven for 45-50 minutes (middle shelf, I cooked for 45 in my oven).","url":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/#instruction-step-5"}],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT45M","totalTime":"PT1H","recipeYield":"8","recipeCategory":"Cake","cookingMethod":"Baking","recipeCuisine":"Healthy","suitableForDiet":"GlutenFreeDiet","aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","reviewCount":"7","ratingValue":"4.4"},"nutrition":{"servingSize":"1 slice","calories":"283 calories","sugarContent":"5.8 g","sodiumContent":"34 mg","fatContent":"22.5 g","saturatedFatContent":"13.6 g","transFatContent":"0 g","carbohydrateContent":"12.6 g","fiberContent":"3 g","proteinContent":"6.4 g","cholesterolContent":"81.8 mg","@type":"nutritionInformation"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Evita"},"datePublished":"2016-10-14","reviewBody":"Looks delicious! Can I freeze it?"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Julie Heron"},"datePublished":"2016-11-08","reviewBody":"This is my first ever gluten free cake with those flours ! Quite a nice cake but a little OTT with the desicated coconut. Is there anything else I can use instead of that? Other than that, a nice texture and very light. Have you any other recipes ???"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kym Matek"},"datePublished":"2017-04-16","reviewBody":"Wow, this cake is now my go to cake for EVERY occasion. It is super easy, delicious, moist and did I say mind blowing yum! When I first assembled it I thought it was going to be dry as the batter was really thick however it was perfect. I didn't have any orange so I just used the juice of 1 lemon. \r\nThank you for a clean recipe for a cake that I can eat and love  ‚ù§Ô∏è that loves me back."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"3"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"georgia"},"datePublished":"2017-12-27","reviewBody":"Not bad, but miss something in flavor."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"T Jean Peters"},"datePublished":"2019-04-19","reviewBody":"Was questioning the ‚Äò 1 tablespoon vanilla ‚Äò (seemed like a lot!) but since no one has mentioned it as a problem, I going w it. I‚Äôve been using your recipes for years, never a problem! Thanks for your hard work.."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Carolyn"},"datePublished":"2019-06-01","reviewBody":"I made these they‚Äôre really nice.  I put them in for the time required on the timer on the oven temperature it says, but I could smell after 25mins-30 mins and they were done but slightly dark on the outside!  Not burnt luckily but dark.  Should have known better, I made them into friands, should have known theyd need less time ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kavita"},"datePublished":"2020-04-01","reviewBody":"Made this with frozen berries - was amazing. Just wondering - could I make as muffins? I'd like to get individual cakes."}],"datePublished":"2014-05-06","@id":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.cookedandloved.com/recipes/paleo-raspberry-coconut-cake/"}]}</script>
